---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import { LlmsGenerator } from '../../components/seo-tools/llms/LlmsGenerator';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="LLMs.txt Generator - Create AI-Friendly Site Descriptions | AICW.io"
  description="Generate llms.txt files for free. Help AI assistants like ChatGPT and Claude understand your website with structured information."
  keywords="llms.txt, llms-txt generator, AI SEO, ChatGPT, Claude, AI assistant, structured data"
>
  <Navigation />

  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-7xl">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <nav class="flex text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-gray-700">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/tools/" class="hover:text-gray-700">Tools</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-900">LLMs.txt Generator</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">LLMs.txt Generator</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl">
        Create an llms.txt file to help AI assistants understand your website. Provide structured
        information about your site, key links, and important content.
      </p>
    </div>

    <LlmsGenerator client:load />

    <section class="mt-12 prose prose-gray max-w-none">
      <h2>What is llms.txt?</h2>
      <p>
        The llms.txt file is a proposed standard for helping AI assistants understand websites.
        Similar to how robots.txt tells crawlers what to index, llms.txt tells AI assistants
        what your site is about and what information is most important.
      </p>

      <h3>Why Use llms.txt?</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Better AI Responses:</strong> Help AI assistants give more accurate information about your site</li>
        <li><strong>Control Your Narrative:</strong> Decide what information AI assistants prioritize</li>
        <li><strong>Improved Discoverability:</strong> Make it easier for AI to recommend your content</li>
        <li><strong>Structured Information:</strong> Organize key information in a machine-readable format</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How to Use</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Fill in your site information (title, tagline, URL)</li>
        <li>Write a comprehensive overview of your site</li>
        <li>Add your most important links</li>
        <li>Optionally add custom sections for additional information</li>
        <li>Download the generated llms.txt file</li>
        <li>Place it at the root of your domain (e.g., https://example.com/llms.txt)</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Best Practices</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep your overview concise but informative (50-200 words)</li>
        <li>Include links to your most important pages</li>
        <li>Update the file when your site structure changes</li>
        <li>Use clear, descriptive language that AI can understand</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
